[[File:PE-mapa-Panelas.png|thumb|right|300px|Location of Panelas within Pernambuco.]] '''Panelas''' is a city located in the state of [[Pernambuco]], [[Brazil]]. Located at 182.6&nbsp;km away from [[Recife]], capital of the state of Pernambuco. Has an estimated ([[Brazilian Institute of Geography and Statistics|Ibge 2009]]) population of 25.500 inhabitants.
==Geography== * State - [[Pernambuco]] * Region - [[Agreste|Agreste Pernambucano]] * Boundaries - [[Altinho, Pernambuco|Altinho]] ('''N'''); [[Quipapá]] and [[Jurema, Pernambuco|Jurema]] ('''S'''); [[Lagoa dos Gatos]], [[São Benedito do Sul]] and [[Cupira, Pernambuco|Cupira]] ('''E'''); [[Ibirajuba]] ('''W'''). * Area - 371.16&nbsp;km<sup>2</sup> * Elevation - 532 m * Hydrography - [[Una River (Pernambuco)|Una River]] * Vegetation - [[Caatinga]] [[Hipoxerófila]] * Climate - [[Tropical]] hot and humid * Annual average temperature - 21.9 c * Distance to [[Recife]] - 182.6&nbsp;km
==Economy== The main economic activities in '''Panelas''' are based in [[agribusiness]], especially [[sugarcane]], [[manioc]]; and [[livestock]] such as [[cattle]], [[goats]], [[sheep]] and [[poultry]].
